value.title: Republicans demand probe into Padilla's $35M grant to Biden-linked firm, claim 'misuse' of taxpayer funds
value.excerpt: EXCLUSIVE: Republicans on the House Oversight and House Administration Committees are demanding answers from California Secretary of State Alex Padilla, who has emerged the frontrunner to be appointed to Vice President-elect Kamala Harris’ Senate seat, about a “highly questionable” $35 million contract

value.title: Wikipedia page for Biden's new Covid czar scrubbed of politically damaging material
value.excerpt: A Democratic consulting firm made numerous changes to Jeff Zients' page as he became a more important figure on Biden’s team this summer and fall.

value.title: Trump campaign, RNC raise $207.5 million since Election Day
value.excerpt: EXCLUSIVE: The Trump campaign, the Republican National Committee, their joint-fundraising committees and President Trump’s new PAC Save America raised a whopping $207.5 million since Election Day, Fox News has learned.

value.title: Former Reagan campaign director Ed Rollins slams pro-Trump attorney as 'glorified ambulance chaser'
value.excerpt: Former Reagan campaign director Ed Rollins slammed President Trump's formal and allied legal teams on Fox News Radio's "The Brian Kilmeade Show" Thursday, at one point calling attorney Lin Wood a "glorified ambulance chaser."

value.title: Hemingway: Trump tackling election integrity issue 'unites Republican voters like nothing else'
value.excerpt: Republicans have been "concerned" with preserving election integrity prior to the 2020 presidential election, Mollie Hemingway said on Thursday.

value.title: 'An attempt to sabotage': Trump's potential purge of career employees casts pall across federal government
value.excerpt: Federal career employees across the Trump administration are fearful of losing their job protections and potentially their jobs, as agencies begin to implement a recent executive order signed by President Donald Trump.

value.title: Ratcliffe urges Biden to let Durham probe run its course, says more docs 'should be' declassified
value.excerpt: EXCLUSIVE: Director of National Intelligence John Ratcliffe on Thursday urged President-elect Joe Biden to allow Special Counsel John Durham's investigation into the origins of the Russia probe to run its course, while saying he hopes there will be "folks held accountable that should be."

value.title: AOC 'Squad' member says hearing of these two possible Biden Cabinet picks 'makes my skin crawl'
value.excerpt: Congressman-elect Jamaal Bowman, D-N.Y., on Thursday said he was satisfied with some of President-elect Joe Biden’s Cabinet picks, but others made his “skin crawl.”

value.title: Trump Administration Claims Facebook Improperly Reserved Jobs for H-1B Workers
value.excerpt: A Justice Department lawsuit accuses the social-media company of illegally reserving high-paying jobs for immigrant workers it was sponsoring for permanent residence and failing to adequately search for U.

value.title: Senate vote likely next week on blocking Trump's massive UAE arms sale
value.excerpt: The top Democrat on the U.S. Senate Foreign Relations Committee said he expected lawmakers would vote as soon as next week on resolutions seeking to block Republican President Donald Trump's $23 billion weapons sale to the United Arab Emirates.

value.title: Ivanka Trump confirms she was questioned by the D.C. attorney general’s office over Inaugural Committee spending
value.excerpt: The president’s daughter released an email showing that she told Trump hotel executives to charge “market price.” The hotel is accused of overcharging.

value.title: Jeffrey Zients expected to be named Biden's coronavirus coordinator
value.excerpt: Jeffrey Zients is President-elect Joe Biden's choice to be the White House coronavirus coordinator, or "czar," a source familiar tells CNN.

value.title: Health officials lay out wish list for Biden Administration: Restore the CDC, prioritize health across the globe
value.excerpt: A who's who of health officials published a commentary Wednesday outlining their wish list for the incoming Biden-Harris Administration, starting with their desire for the U.S. to rejoin the global public health community.

value.title: Kamala Harris picks Tina Flournoy to be her chief of staff
value.excerpt: Vice President-elect Kamala Harris has named veteran Democratic strategist Tina Flournoy as her chief of staff.

value.title: Trump awards football coach Lou Holtz the Medal of Freedom
value.excerpt: President Donald Trump awarded the Medal of Freedom to former football coach Lou Holtz on Thursday in an Oval Office ceremony.

value.title: Iran says it will comply with nuclear deal if Biden lifts all sanctions
value.excerpt: Foreign minister calls on US to ‘show its good faith’ but appears to rule out renegotiating deal

value.title: 'Simply unthinkable': Law officers call for halt to executions in Trump's final weeks
value.excerpt: Five executions are scheduled before Biden, who opposes capital punishment, takes office. Ninety current and former law officials want them to stop.

value.title: Trump campaign’s star witness in Michigan was deemed ‘not credible.’ Then, her loud testimony went viral.
value.excerpt: Even Giuliani reportedly made a point to note he had just met Melissa Carone, whose testimony drew comparisons to SNL sketches.

value.title: Explainer: Could Trump preemptively pardon his family — or even himself?
value.excerpt: U.S. President Donald Trump's pardoning of his former adviser Michael Flynn has fueled speculation over whether the president could pardon other associates, and even members of his family, during his final weeks in office.

value.title: Gaetz accuses Biden of wanting to be 'valet for the establishment in both parties'
value.excerpt: An unusual and seemingly unlikely coalition of progressive Democrats and populist Republicans could form an alliance to be reckoned with in the new Congress next year, Rep. Matt Gaetz, R-Fla. told "The Ingraham Angle" Wednesday.

value.title: Comey to teach at Columbia Law School alongside professor who leaked Trump memo
value.excerpt: Ex-FBI chief to teach a seminar called “Lawyers and Leaders.”

value.title: Ivanka Trump was deposed Tuesday in DC attorney general's inauguration lawsuit
value.excerpt: Ivanka Trump, the President's daughter and adviser, sat for a deposition Tuesday with investigators from the Washington, DC, attorney general's office as part of its lawsuit alleging the misuse of inaugural funds, according to a court filing.

value.title: Gov. Michelle Lujan Grisham turned down Biden administration post, sources say
value.excerpt: The Democratic governor of New Mexico is rumored to be a contender for a separate position in the administration.

value.title: Pro-Trump attorneys Sidney Powell, Lin Wood urge Georgians not to vote in Senate runoffs without changes
value.excerpt: Powell and Wood are not working for the Trump campaign in an official capacity.

value.title: Biden’s stern warning: ‘You cannot be traveling during … holidays’
value.excerpt: President-elect Joe Biden says he doesn’t “want to scare anybody,” but he’s pleading with Americans to not travel during the upcoming holiday season.
